<style>
  .article_column-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 320px;
    border-radius: 11px;
  }
  img.article_column-image {
    overflow: hidden;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: 50% 50%;
  }
  .article_column-image-border {
    border: 1px solid rgba(60, 31, 27, 0.30);
  }
  .article_column {
      height: max-content;
  }
  .article_column-third {
    width: calc(33.3333334% - 33.3333334px);
  }
  .article_column-half {
    width: calc(50% - 25px);
  }
  .article_column-text-third-top {
    padding-top: 81px;
  }
  .article_column-text ul {
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
    color: #3c1f1b;
    margin-top: -10px;
    padding-left: 34px;
  }
  @media(max-width: 1450px) {
    .article_column-half {
    width: calc(50% - 15px);
  }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
      gap: 30px;
    }
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 114px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 1250px) {
    .article_column-third {
        width: calc(50% - 15px);
    }
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 81px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 950px) {
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 114px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 750px) {
    .article_column-text ul {
      margin-top: -12px;
      padding-left: 32px;
    }
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 0;
    }
    .article_column-half {
      width: 100%
    }
    .article_column-third {
        width: 100%;
        gap: 30px;
    }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
        gap: 30px;
    }
    .rebranding_container {
        gap: 40px;
    }
    .article_column-text .h3-heading-pp, .article_column-text .h3-heading-ss {
        text-align: center;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 450px) {
    .article_column-image {
      height: 250px;
    }
  }
</style>

<div class="rebranding_container block-flex-wrap block-gap-50">
  <div class="rebranding-section-title block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center">
    <h2 class="h2-heading-ss">
      How to Identify a 
      <span class="h2-heading-pp">
        Fake Balenciaga Bag
      </span>
      : 6 Key Signs to Spot a Counterfeit
    </h2>
    <p class="body-text block-max-width">
      Balenciaga bags are known for their premium quality, iconic design, and luxurious feel. Unfortunately, this makes them a common target for counterfeiters. If you're wondering <strong>how to tell if a Balenciaga bag is fake</strong>, this guide will help you recognize the most common signs of a fake Balenciaga handbag.
<br><br>
Whether you're buying secondhand or just verifying an existing piece, 
here are six essential things to look for:
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="article_columns-wrapp block-flex-wrap block-gap-50 block-flex-start-center">
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "balenciaga-blog_seo-1.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Balenciaga Bag: Poor Quality Materials and Craftsmanship">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 1</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Poor Quality Materials and Craftsmanship</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
         Authentic Balenciaga bags are crafted from high-quality lambskin, calfskin and goatskin leather, with a soft, yet durable feel. In contrast, fake Balenciaga bags often use synthetic or low-grade leather that feels stiff, plasticky, or overly shiny.
        <br><br>
        <span class="italic"><strong>Tip:</strong> If the material feels cheap or smells like chemicals, it’s likely a replica.</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "balenciaga-blog_seo-2.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Balenciaga Bag: Inconsistent or Missing Serial Numbers">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 2</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Inconsistent or Missing Serial Numbers</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Every genuine Balenciaga bag features a <strong>serial number</strong> on the inside leather tag, usually accompanied by a <strong>“Balenciaga.Paris”</strong> stamp. The number is typically consistent with the bag model and style.
          <br><br>
          Common red flags:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Serial number is missing or smudged</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Font appears off or inconsistent</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">No model number or misplaced numbers</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "balenciaga-blog_seo-3.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Balenciaga Bag: Misspelled or Incorrect Logos and Branding">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 3</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Misspelled or Incorrect Logos and Branding</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          One of the easiest ways to spot a fake is by examining the branding. <strong>Real Balenciaga logos</strong> are:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Clean</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Evenly spaced</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Correctly spelled</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Fake versions might have:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text"><strong>Misspelled brand names</strong></p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Incorrect font weight or alignment</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Poorly stamped or printed logos</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "balenciaga-blog_seo-4.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Balenciaga Bag: Cheap or Lightweight Hardware">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 4</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Cheap or Lightweight Hardware</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Authentic Balenciaga bags use <strong>heavy-duty brass or aged hardware</strong>. Zippers, buckles, and studs should feel substantial and operate smoothly.
<br><br>
Telltale counterfeit signs include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Flimsy, lightweight metal</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Loose fittings</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Discoloration or peeling after light use</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "balenciaga-blog_seo-5.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Balenciaga Bag: Uneven or Sloppy Stitching">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 5</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Uneven or Sloppy Stitching</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          The stitching on a real Balenciaga bag is tight, even, and meticulously done. Count the stitches — they’re typically consistent on each panel.
          <br><br>
          Look out for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Irregular spacing</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Loose threads</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Crooked lines</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "balenciaga-blog_seo-6.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Balenciaga Bag: Lack of Attention to Detail">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 6</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Lack of Attention to Detail</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Balenciaga is known for precision. Elements like <strong>the lining, zipper pulls, and interior tags</strong> are always neatly finished. 
<br><br>
A fake bag may have:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Misaligned pockets</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Poorly glued elements</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Crooked or rushed finishing work</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

